Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine light brown; grey core; some mica. Rectangular stamp with anchor symbol.
Type series: KT639 (Virginia Grace's unpublished K(nidian) T(ype) series)
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 101a, 14. Name Eukrates.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0276)
